
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `bzcat` baraye chap kardane file-haye `bzip2` shode be shekle sade (standard output) estefade mishavad. Yani file-haye zipeede shode ro baz mikone va mohtaviyate anha ro neshoon mide, bedune inke file asli ro tagheer bede.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `bzcat file.bz2` --> 📤 Chap kardane mohtaviyate file `file.bz2`.
    🔹 `bzcat file1.bz2 file2.bz2` --> 📃 Chap kardane mohtaviyate chand file be tartib.
    🔹 `bzcat --help` --> ❓ Namayeshe rahnamaye dastoor.
    🔹 `bzcat --version` --> ℹ️ Namayeshe version-e `bzcat`.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ bzcat myfile.bz2

    🔹 Chap kardane mohtaviyate file `myfile.bz2` dar terminal.

    $ bzcat file1.bz2 file2.bz2 > combined_file.txt

    🔹 Chap kardane mohtaviyate `file1.bz2` va `file2.bz2` va zakhire kardane anha dar `combined_file.txt`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ bzcat logfile.bz2 | grep "error"

    🔹 Chap kardane mohtaviyate `logfile.bz2` va estefade az `grep` baraye jostojooye khat-haie ke dar anha "error" vojood darad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `bzcat` command is used to print `bzip2` compressed files to standard output. It essentially decompresses the files and displays their contents without modifying the original compressed file.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `bzcat file.bz2` --> 📤 Prints the content of `file.bz2`.
    🔹 `bzcat file1.bz2 file2.bz2` --> 📃 Prints the content of multiple files sequentially.
    🔹 `bzcat --help` --> ❓ Displays the command's help information.
    🔹 `bzcat --version` --> ℹ️ Displays the version of `bzcat`.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ bzcat myfile.bz2

    🔹 Prints the content of `myfile.bz2` to the terminal.

    $ bzcat file1.bz2 file2.bz2 > combined_file.txt

    🔹 Prints the content of `file1.bz2` and `file2.bz2` and saves it to `combined_file.txt`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ bzcat logfile.bz2 | grep "error"

    🔹 Prints the content of `logfile.bz2` and uses `grep` to search for lines containing "error".
